President Trump and newly appointed National Security Advisor Robert O'Brien made remarks at Los Angeles International Airport. They discussed their successful track record with hostage negotiations and the importance of peace through strength in foreign policy. They also addressed the situation in Saudi Arabia and the possibility of a military strike on Iran. President Trump stated that his thinking on the matter has not changed and that the United States has a strong military. He did not provide details on potential actions but mentioned the upcoming announcement of significant sanctions on Iran. The President emphasized that the ultimate option refers to war, not a nuclear strike. O'Brien was praised for his expertise in hostage negotiations, and the President expressed confidence in their chemistry and future relationship. The President also mentioned his upcoming visit to the border to showcase the progress on wall construction. He noted that he has not spoken to Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu regarding the election results in Israel.